          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a kind of manual or handbook to be consulted by a priest, outlining rules (religious laws) for the performance of three different kinds of fire sacrifices and prayers offered to the planets. Each sacrifice (Ayutahomapaddhati, Lakṣahoma, and Koṭihoma) is treated separately.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Grahayajñatraya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">ग्रहयज्ञत्रय</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Jayata, son of Valabhadra</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti koṭihoma // vyalekhīdaṃ grahayajñatrayaṃ dhīrādhirājadhārmikālokaśrīmatpaṃḍitavalabhaḍrasūnājayatena // (f. 5r).</colophon>
